{"/service/ndnp/txdn/batch_txdn_krum_ver01/data/sn86090238/00517175596/1910121601/1016.xml":{"full_text":"POWDER\nAbsolutely Pure\nThe only baking powder\nmade from Royal Grape\nOream of Tartar\nNo Alum, No Lime Phosphite\nPOLITICS NOT ON.\nPUBLIC HIND NOW\nMonta J. Moore of Cameron, who\nmade the race against Thomas Camp\nbell for the nomination of governor\non the democratic ticket four years\nago, is registered at the Menger, hav\ning come from his home to this city\non a business trip.\nDiscussing the political situation in\nthe state, Mr. Moore said:\n\u201cThere Is very little just now in\npolitical circles to attract attention.\nThe people are all interested in the\nhoUday season and when this is the\ncase a lull in things political always\nresults. The appointments so far\nmade by Governor-elect Colquitt ap\npear to have met the approval of the\npeople.\n\"The prosperity in my part of the\nstate is attracting more attention just\nnow than politics. Farmers have\nbeen rewarded with a larger crop than\nthey anticipated and received splendid\nprices for all they had to sell. The ef\nfect of this is evident everywhere.\nFarmers are out of debt and are sat\nisfied with the year\u2019s work. Some are\nbuying more land and others are mak\ning broader development on what they\nhave. Many splendid homes are go\ning up in the agricultural section and\nthere is a general air of prosperity\neverywhere. The towns and cities feel\nthe effect of this and are correspond\ningly prosperous. Taking the year as\na whole, it has been the most pros\nperous In the history of the section,\nand everyone feels good as a result.\nThe outlook could not be better than\nIt Is today In the vicinity of Cam\neron.\u2019\u2019\nLEACH SEES PROSPERITY.\nT. G. N. Freight Agent Pleased With\nBusiness Outlook in 'Texas\nfor 1911.\nN. M. Leach, general freight agent\nfor the I. G. N., with headquarters\nin Palestine, arrived in San Antonio\nyesterday to inspect the local freight\ndepartment. He expressed himself as\npleased with the business outlook for\nTexas In 1911. He said that conditions\nall through the state are better than\nthey were a year ago at this time.\nParticularly East Texas has stood up\nwell under the long drouth which\nprevailed all over Texas during the\nspring and summer months.\n\u201cThis rain we are having means\nmillions of dollars to Texas,\u201d he re\nmarked, \"If it only continues a lit\ntle longer there is no reason why the\nstate should not produce a bumper\ncrop next year.\u201d\nMr. Leach will leave tonight for\nPalestine.\nMEDICOS TO ELECT.\n\nOfficers of Bexar County Medical As\nsociation Will be Chosen at\nMeeting Tonight.\nTonight the Bexar County Medical\nassociation will meet and elect of\nficers for the coming year. The meet\ning will be held at the International\nclub and will be called to order at\n8:30 o\u2019clock. Following the election a\nThe London Lancet, after a careful examination of\nScott\u2019s Emulsion\nreported that \"the preparation fulfills ALL the requirement* and\npresent* ALL the condition* ot a very utisfactory emulsion. In\nappearance and consistency It I* not unlike cream and under\nthe microscope the fat globule* are seen to be of perfectly regular\nsire and unifermly distributed Sorrell has the oil been emulsi\nfied that even when shaken with water the fat is slow to separate.\nThe taste is decidedly unobjectionable and the Emulsion should\nprove an excellent food as well as a tonic.''\nWo believe no other preparation of Cod Liver Oil ha*\nreceived such weighty commendation and if the same high au\nthorities were to examine it now they would find it even finer,\nmore digestible, more palatable and more satisfactory in every\nways in fact, SCOTTS EMULSION ha* so long been the one\nsatisfactory and perfect Emulsion that it is accepted as the\nstandard by medical practitioner* all over the world, by the\npublic and by hundred* of imitators, for it is the one and only\nEmulsion imitated.\nThe imitations are in name only for no ether preparation\nof Cod Liver Oil is so pure, so perfect and so beneficiaL\nSCOTT\u2019S EMULSION\nha* become the world\u2019s Standard Body-Builder because of the\nperfect purity of its ingredients, it* absolute freedom from\nALCOHOL or any other harmful substance and because the\nresults from it are uniform and far greater than from any\nether preparation.\nlUiday.\nONE DAY\u2019S LIST OF\nVOTERS QUALIFIED\nVoters who qualified by obtaininf poll tax receipts or exemption certificate* st the of\nfice of the county tux collector on Wednesday, December 14, 1910, \u00bbre shown below. The ta\nble gives the age of the voter, the length ot residence claimed in the state, county and city,\nhis ward and precinct and the number of the paper issued to him. For example, \u201cP, 27\"\nmeans poll tax receipt Mo. 27, and \u201dX. 10\u201d means exemption certificate No. 16 in the par\nticular precinct.\nVOTERS WHO QUALIFIED WEDNESDAY, DECEMBER 14, 1910.\nNo No. \u2014Yrs. Res. in\u2014\nName and address Age. Ward. Prec. Paper. State. Co. City\nAbolos, Jose, 1002 Monterey 27 2 7 P. 63 27 27 27\nAguilar, Sixto, 212 Lake View avenue...,21 3 9 X. 50 21 21 21\nAllensworth, D. C\u201e 201 Macon 41 4 16 P. 58 31 31 31\nArocha, Antonio. 21&H bonth Lgrcdo 47 2 6 P. 83 47 47 47\nArreano, Trinidad, 1000 El Pasd 38 2 5 P. 319 38 2 2\nAvelar, Pedro, 416 North Laredo 46 3 9 P. 88 6 6 6\nBoylan, Rufus, 202 West Commerce 20 1 1 X. 41 5 5 3\nBehms, George, 303 Delgado 3 12 X. 41 20 20 20\nBenites, Jesus, 306 Ruiz 50 3 10 P. 40 50 50 50\nBinz, F., 211 Frasch 42 1 2 P. 69 42 42 42\nBlackstock. B. B., 207 Forrest 1 4 P. 94 25 6 6\nCampo, Adolfo, 1415 West Commerce..... .34 3 10 P. 38 33 33 33\nCardenas, Jose Marie, 533 South Flores...42 1 1 P. 74 33 26 26\nCardona, Juan, 404 South Laredo 24 1 1 P. 82 24 2 2\nCisneros, Antonio, 623 Delgado... .42 3 13 p. 85 35 20 20\nClamp, C. C., 230 West Cypress 55 4 17 P, 58 55 17 17\nClemens, F. A\u201e 133 Rischo 28 1 2 P. 65 2